Nate, I gather from your emails that you live and work in Japan, (lucky you)
do you know if there are any Japanese history groups interested in European
medevil history ? Our counterparts if you like. If so do they have similar
misconceptions about our/my history. We all know that the "chivalrous knight
in shining armour" is largely a myth, the knight being more likely to cause
the damsel distress, than rescue her from it . Do the Japanese groups relies
and discus misconceptions like this, as we do, or is their historic vision
of Europien history less  blured as (some) of ous is about  Japanese
history?  Denny.
